<HL>
   Canada to Sell Four Bond Issues
</HL>
<DATE>
04/17/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C17
</SO>
<CO>
   CANDA
</CO>
<IN>
BOND MARKET NEWS (BON)
</IN>
<LP>
   OTTAWA -- The Canadian government said it will offer 1.5
billion Canadian dollars (US$1.28 billion) of bonds in four
issues this week.
   The sale will include 11.75% bonds due Oct. 15, 1993;
11.75% bonds due March 1, 1995; 11.50% bonds due Sept. 1,
2000; and 11.25% bonds due June 1, 2015. Offering terms are
to be announced today.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The Bank of Canada has agreed to purchase at least C$100
million of the new bonds. The remainder will be available to
public investors.
   Proceeds will be applied toward redemption of C$2.13
billion of government bonds maturing May 1 and for general
government purposes, the Finance Department said.
</TEXT>
